1) "find t=0 from location of the laser pulse" function: input: data set, pump_variable; output: index of t=0;
2) "is it with or without pump" function. 
input: data set; output: 'pump'. 'no pump' probably better to have variable pump with values TRUE or FALSE 
3) box_smoothing - I will write it
4) Savitsky-Galay smoothing - I will write it
5) noise in kinetics: if without pump, take rms; if with pump, 1) take rms for t<0; smooth the kinetics for t>0 -> get smoothed function and subtract it from the real unsmoothed kinetics. It should look like straight flat line-> get rms of it. a) it should be equal to rms for t<0 and smaller than specified treshold. 
6) take dAs and t=0 index. fit the t<0 points with the straight line and save its' parameters and subtract this line from the dA kinetics.

